# Valgrind's bpf() checker validates the FULL union bpf_attr layout for the
# command, ignoring the size argument. This SDK passes truncated attr structs
# (e.g. BPF_MAP_CREATE's first 5 fields, 20 bytes) with the matching size --
# the kernel only reads that many bytes, so bytes past the struct (flagged as
# attr->map_ifindex / attr->map_name) never reach it. ABI-correct; suppress
# the false positive rather than padding every attr to a kernel-version-
# dependent size. Matched by param name with any call stack: optimized builds
# inline quic_xdpbpf_map_create into its callers, so function frames are not
# a stable anchor.
{
   # the param name valgrind uses really has no closing paren (upstream quirk)
   bpf-short-attr-map-ifindex
   Memcheck:Param
   bpf(attr->map_ifindex
   obj:*
}
{
   bpf-short-attr-map-name
   Memcheck:Param
   bpf(attr->map_name)
   obj:*
}
